        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 2:01AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 201 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Monahans, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Odessa Schlemeyer Field, West Odessa, Penwell, Pleasant Farms, and
Odessa.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 97 and 120.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
